	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Tue Aug 01, 2006 5:01 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Debug mode has <strong>always</strong> slowed down emulation, since it has to refresh the pattern table and nametable preview windows, which aren't drawn using optimized code. It also forces the window size to 2x so it can position the other debug windows relative to it without them overlapping.
<br />
<br />Also, what resolution are you running at - 800x600? Even 1024x768 should be just <em>barely</em> too small to fit everything without overlapping, and 1152x864 or higher should have plenty of room. It's not really possible to make it take up less space without actually losing information.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


