<br />
<br />And you're using that with a <strong>1MB</strong> video card? Sorry, but I don't quite believe you - to have <em>that</em> little memory, it would have to be over 10 years old.
<br />
<br />I got my <em>128MB</em> (GeForce FX 5200) video card for less than $50, so there's really no excuse for sticking with whatever you're using unless you literally have no money (in which case you probably wouldn't have an internet connection) or are on a fixed income or something.
<br />
<br />In any event, as far as I'm concerned, the minimum system requirements for Nintendulator include a video card capable of <em>at least</em> 1024x768 with 16-bit color, and I don't intend to lower it. If you can't go beyond 800x600, then I suggest you upgrade your system so it can.

		

